Hello!

I am writing the small plugin for FishEye Version:3.6.1 Build:20141030150539 2014-10-30 and found that I can access all repository properties and options except ExternalAuthSettings - that value cannot be changed using the Java API - only manually and using the FishEye Web interface. Please take a look the sample below:

{code:java}
package com.company.fisheye.restapi;

import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import javax.ws.rs.Consumes;
import javax.ws.rs.POST;
import javax.ws.rs.Path;
import javax.ws.rs.Produces;
import javax.ws.rs.QueryParam;
import javax.ws.rs.core.Context;
import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;
import javax.ws.rs.core.Response;
import javax.ws.rs.core.Response.Status;

import com.atlassian.fisheye.spi.admin.data.ExternalAuthSettings;
import com.atlassian.fisheye.spi.admin.data.LdapAuthSettings;
import com.atlassian.fisheye.spi.admin.data.LdapAuthSettings.MatchType;
import com.atlassian.fisheye.spi.admin.services.RepositoryAdminService;

@Path("/")
@Consumes({ MediaType.APPLICATION_XML, MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON })
@Produces({ MediaType.APPLICATION_XML, MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON })
public class RestCompletionStatusService {

	@Context
	private HttpServletRequest request;

	@Context
	private HttpServletResponse response;

	private final RepositoryAdminService repositoryAdminService;

	public RestCompletionStatusService(
			RepositoryAdminService repositoryAdminService) {
		this.repositoryAdminService = repositoryAdminService;
	}

	@POST
    @Path("setLDAPResctriction")
	@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    public Response setLDAPRestriction(@QueryParam("repoName") String repoName, @Context HttpServletRequest request,
			@Context HttpServletResponse response) {

		String responseData = "";
		//Try 1
		//Get current value
		LdapAuthSettings las = ((LdapAuthSettings) repositoryAdminService.getRepositoryOptions(repoName).getExternalAuthSettings());
		String oldVal = las.getFilter()+", MatchType = "+las.getMatchType();
		//Set new value
		las.setFilter("TEST1");
		las.setMatchType(MatchType.ANY);
		//Test that value is updated
		las = ((LdapAuthSettings) repositoryAdminService.getRepositoryOptions(repoName).getExternalAuthSettings());
		String newVal = las.getFilter()+", MatchType = "+las.getMatchType();
		responseData+="Test1 \nOld VAL = "+oldVal+",\nNew VAL = "+newVal+"\n\n";
		
		//Try 2
		//Get the current value
		oldVal = newVal;
		//Create new object and update repository options
		ExternalAuthSettings eas = new LdapAuthSettings("TEST2", MatchType.ANY);
		repositoryAdminService.getRepositoryOptions(repoName).setExternalAuthSettings(eas);
		//Test that value is updated
		las = ((LdapAuthSettings) repositoryAdminService.getRepositoryOptions(repoName).getExternalAuthSettings());
		newVal = las.getFilter()+", MatchType = "+las.getMatchType();
		responseData+="Test2 \nOld VAL = "+oldVal+",\nNew VAL = "+newVal;

		return Response.status(Status.OK).entity(responseData).build();
		
    }
}
{code}

Then I test the new REST method with CURL:
{code}
curl -X POST --user *******:******* "http://localhost:8060/rest/myendpoint/1.0/setLDAPResctriction?repoName=test"
{code}

The result:
{code}
Test1
Old VAL = (&(sAMAccountName=${USERNAME})(objectClass=user)), MatchType = USER,
New VAL = (&(sAMAccountName=${USERNAME})(objectClass=user)), MatchType = USER

Test2
Old VAL = (&(sAMAccountName=${USERNAME})(objectClass=user)), MatchType = USER,
New VAL = (&(sAMAccountName=${USERNAME})(objectClass=user)), MatchType = USER
{code}

where 
{code}
(&(sAMAccountName=${USERNAME})(objectClass=user)), MatchType = USER
{code}
is the value that I set before using the web interface of FishEye.

May be there should be some update method for persisting my changes, but I cannot find the documentation about it. Anyway, all other changes are persisted immediately.

